Board of Directors















































Search & Hit Enter 





HomeNEXT CompaniesNEXT Financial Group, Inc.Visionary Asset ManagementNFISCOCareers with NEXTBenefitsOpen PositionsBoard of Directors























Board of Directors



Chairman




Norman Grant Norman Grant is the Chairman & CEO of NEXT Financial Holdings, Inc. He has had 34 years of experience in the investment business as a personal producer and OSJ Branch Manager. He earned his CFP™ degree in 1990. Norman serves on NEXT’s Acquisitions & Development committee, the VAM committee, the RIA committee, the Budget committee, the Risk Assessment committee and chairs the Compliance Advisory Board. He is an original founder of NEXT and has served on the Board since inception.



Directors




Cary Cowan Cary has over 40 years in the financial services field as a personal producer and as an OSJ Branch Manager. Cary holds the CLU, CHFC, CFP® and CWS® designations. He serves on the Acquisitions & Development committee, the VAM committee, the RIA Committee, the Insurance committee and the Acquisition Due Diligence committee. Cary joined NEXT in June 2003 and has been a member of the board since March 2006.



David Holtz Dave has 34 years in financial services with 25 of those years as a Division Manager. A 1971 Penn State graduate with a B.S. in Marketing, he acquired the Certified Financial Planner™ designation in 1986 from the College for Financial Planning and maintains a largely fee-based practice.. Dave serves on NEXT's Compliance Advisory Board, IT Advisory Board, Acquisitions & Development committee, Information Technology committee and Compliance committee. He is an original founder of NEXT and has served on the Board since inception.



Jeffrey Saline Jeffrey is a board member with NEXT Financial Holdings, Inc. This appointment is in recognition of his instrumental contribution to shaping and expanding the collective companies. In addition to helping NEXT become a seven-time Broker/Dealer of the Year, he has been consistently recognized amongst the top five financial advisors within his broker dealer NEXT Financial Group based upon production over the past five years.  *Based on a poll of registered representatives conducted by Investment Advisor magazine.Broker/Dealers rated highest by their representatives are awarded "Broker/Dealer(B/D) of the Year.



John Untereker John Untereker joined NEXT Financial Holdings in 2016. He has an extensive business background which spans across decades of experience in executive positions where he developed expertise in financial reporting, public company governance, debt and equity financing, mergers and acquisitions and financial systems. John began his impressive career in the New York office of PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC). John has also held key financial roles, including Chief Financial Officer (CFO). He currently serves as Executive Vice President and COO/CFO of Preventice Solutions, Inc. and was President and COO/CFO at eCardio Diagnostics, LLC from October 2009 to September 2014.



 




















