NEXT Financial Holdings, Inc. Introduces National Sales and Relationship DirectorHomeMailFlickrTumblrNewsSportsFinanceCelebrityAnswersGroupsMobileMoreYahooSearchSearchSkip to NavigationSkip to Main ContentSkip to Related Content0NEXT Financial Holdings, Inc. Introduces National Sales and Relationship DirectorMarketwireDecember 21, 2010ReblogShareTweetShareHOUSTON, TX--(Marketwire - 12/21/10) - NEXT Financial Holdings, Inc. welcomes Sherry E. Pitts into the position of National Sales and Relationship Director. Her new and evolving role in the company is to engage, motivate and advise seven-time Broker/Dealer of the Year* winner NEXT Financial Group, Inc. ("NEXT") registered representatives on every aspect of their business while simultaneously growing all subsidiaries under NEXT Financial Holdings, Inc.Sherry is a top-ranked sales and business development professional specializing in financial investments and consumer lending. Using a consultative approach, she utilizes her solid product knowledge to help increase registered representatives gross dealer concessions."My passion is to help people. Having 17 years of experience in the financial industry, I've acquired the ability to listen and provide creative solutions to people using the utmost integrity," said Pitts.Having a complimentary background in banking, institutional fixed income sales, and internal and external wholesales; Sherry has developed a powerful platform to effectively build strong referral bases through integrity, superior service and expertise in managing client relationships."Sherry will be a powerful resource for our reps. She has the knowledge and know-how to successfully get our reps where they want to be in their business," said Kimberly Branch, CFP, CLTC, President of 4WARD Financial Marketing, a subsidiary under NEXT Financial Holdings, Inc.Sherry holds a Bachelor of Science in Psychology from Georgia State University and Series 7 and 63 licenses.NEXT is a truly independent broker/dealer. They are a unique firm founded, owned, and managed by their representatives. It is designed to serve the best interests of their representatives: people who share a passion for investing and the desire to be an owner of a company they believe in. NEXT offers a wide array of products enabling representatives to provide advice in the best interest of their clients.For more information, contact Adrienne Zientek at 713-375-2592, or email: azientek@4wardfm.com*Based on a poll of registered representatives conducted by Investment Advisor magazine. Broker/Dealers rated highest by their representatives are awarded "Broker/Dealer (B/D) of the Year."www.nextfinancial.comReblogShareTweetSharePopular in the CommunityAngelina Jolie Reveals Bell’s Palsy Diagnosis — As She Says Children Are Still ‘Healing’ From Brad Pitt Divorce3,120 reactions5%72%23%Trunk Club. Making Sense of Style.Trunk ClubSponsoredSmuggled animals24 reactions0%75%25%These Sorority Sisters Did a ‘Melanin Illustrated’ Photo Shoot803 reactions7%63%30%White House threatens to shut down briefing over questions on transgender policy shift7,071 reactions4%69%27%Discover it: 4.8 out of 5 avg. by 24K+ customersDiscover CardSponsoredColorado woman defies Immigration and Customs Enforcement from church sanctuary103 reactions5%72%23%Ohio State Fair ride incident leaves one dead, multiple injured3 reactions0%100%0%Luis Fonsi On Justin Bieber's Spanish, 'Despacito' Hitting No. 1518 reactions4%79%17%Engineer Finds Pattern; Makes Millions in StocksMoney MorningSponsoredKristin Beck, transgender Navy SEAL hero: 'Let's meet face to face and you tell me I'm not worthy'12,117 reactions4%66%30%Officials: Fair ride that broke apart passed inspections210 reactions4%77%19%Man Killed by Wife and Son, Who Then Used Drain Cleaner to Burn His Face So He Wouldn't Be Identified470 reactions5%69%26%Women Everywhere Should Carry This Tiny DeviceSiren SongSponsoredWildfires force French Riviera evacuations43 reactions4%71%25%NFL player Lucky 